Is an encrypted communication channel (wss) used?
Are the data received from the client via WebSocket protocol validated?
Does the WebSocket server used limit the number of possible parallel connections from one client?
How is the authentication and authorization for resources made available through WebSocket implemented?
Is a known WebSocket server or proprietary solution used? Has the original server passed the stage of security verification?
Do we have an implemented CSP policy limiting the sources with which we can establish a connection?
Is the Origin header validated on the server side, also taking into account the fact that it can be manipulated when using a client that is not a web browser?
Is a boiled library serving the client and server part responsibl efor the WebSocket protocol used?
Does the firewall allow network traffic to the port on which the WebSocket server is listening, only from specific sources?
